title: Cardinals climb to sixth in state polls ahead of battle with Forks
text:
Cardinals climb to sixth in state polls ahead of battle with Forks 
By wbng sports Cardinals climb to sixth in state polls ahead of battle with Forks October 7, 2015 Updated Oct 7, 2015 at 2:14 PM EDT 
(WBNG Binghamton) Newark Valley has climbed up to No. 6 in the state in Class C in the latest New York State Sportswriters Association rankings ahead of a blockbuster match up with top-ranked Chenango Forks on Saturday. 
The Cardinals moved up three spots this week after holding off Greene last Saturday to remain unbeaten. 
WBNG E-News - Sign Up For Our Newsletter! 
Saturday's game between the Blue Devils and Cardinals is at Newark Valley at 1:30 p.m. 
Newark Valley and Chenango Forks are two of ten Section IV teams ranked in the latest polls that were released on Wednesday. 
As expected, Maine-Endwell remains the top team in Class A. The Spartans won their 56th straight game last Friday against Johnson City. 
In Class D, four teams remain ranked. Deposit/Hancock is the top of the group, ranking fourth in the state.
